End Process

Process called "test_macho_write_header" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    T.begin_suite(results, "macho_write_header")

    Let builder be ExeFormat.create_macho_builder(16777223)
    T.assert_not_null(results, "Mach-O builder created", builder)

    Note: Write a Mach-O header with 2 commands, 200 bytes of commands
    Let result be ExeFormat.macho_write_header(builder, 2, 200)
    T.assert_equal(results, "macho_write_header returns 1", result, 1)

    Note: Verify the output starts with Mach-O magic: 0xFEEDFACF
    Note: In LE: CF FA ED FE
    Let tracker be __load(builder, 0)
    Let buf be __load(tracker, 0)

    Let b0 be __load8(buf, 0)
    Let b1 be __load8(buf, 1)
    Let b2 be __load8(buf, 2)
    Let b3 be __load8(buf, 3)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Mach-O magic byte 0 is 0xCF (207)", b0, 207)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Mach-O magic byte 1 is 0xFA (250)", b1, 250)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Mach-O magic byte 2 is 0xED (237)", b2, 237)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Mach-O magic byte 3 is 0xFE (254)", b3, 254)

    Note: Header should be 32 bytes (Mach-O 64-bit header)
    Let pos be __load(tracker, 8)
    T.assert_equal(results, "Mach-O header is 32 bytes", pos, 32)

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "test_macho_build_executable" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
